# Project Conventions

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) with React 19
- **Content**: Fumadocs MDX (fumadocs-mdx v14, fumadocs-core v16, fumadocs-ui v16)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with Fumadocs neutral theme preset
- **Fonts**: Inter (body) + Instrument Serif (display), loaded via `next/font/google`
- **Deployment**: Vercel (standard Next.js, no special config)

## Content Structure
- Content lives in `content/docs/` as `.mdx` files with YAML frontmatter (`title`, `description`)
- Navigation is controlled by `meta.json` files in each content folder
- Content source configured in `source.config.ts`, loaded via `lib/source.ts`
- The manuscript source of truth lives in a separate repo (`trilogy-project/manuscript/`)

## IDEAL Framework (Content Organization)
- 5 stages: Identify, Diagnose, Earn, Assess, Lock
- 3 modules per stage (15 total) + 5 stage openings + 5 stage closings
- 2 extensions + 1 closing chapter = 30 content pages total
- Sidebar order: Overview > Stage 1-5 > Extensions > Closing

## Route Structure
- `/` — Landing page (`app/(home)/page.tsx`)
- `/docs` — Documentation index (Introduction)
- `/docs/[...slug]` — All doc pages
- `/api/search` — Orama search endpoint

## File Organization
- `app/(home)/` — Landing page and home layout
- `app/docs/` — Documentation layout and catch-all page
- `app/api/` — API routes (search)
- `content/docs/` — MDX content files + meta.json navigation
- `lib/source.ts` — Fumadocs content loader
- `components/mdx.tsx` — MDX component overrides
- `scripts/` — Build and audit scripts

## Content Frontmatter
Every MDX file requires:
```yaml
---
title: "Page Title"
description: "One-line description for SEO and page header."
---
```

## Known MDX Caveats
- `# ` at the start of a list item is parsed as a heading. Escape as `\#` or rewrite as "Number of".
- The `compiled/Chapters.md` legacy file from the manuscript is excluded from the doc site.
- Fumadocs renders the frontmatter `title` as the page H1. Do not include an H1 in the MDX body.